[Appenzell Outer Rhodes is a German-speaking canton in the northeast of Switzerland, close to the territories of Liechtenstein, Germany (Bavaria), and Austria (Vorarlberg); see map at http://www.deutsche-schutzgebiete.de/webpages/Appenzell-Ausserrhoden_Karte_1914_XX.gif. - Mod.AS]

******
[2] Liechtenstein: suspected
Date: Fri 27 Sep 2013
Source: Radio L, Liechtenstein [in German, trans. submitter SZ, edited]
http://www.radio.li/de/nachrichten/nachrichten-detailseite/artikel/5232/


Cattle from Liechtenstein and Switzerland might have become infected with the disease in Vorarlberg (Austria). There is a possibility that the animals became infected through contact with wildlife at Lech in [the valley of] Montafon. 4 animals tested positive of which 2 have already been slaughtered.

There is only a small risk for humans.

